data.title: A Long Time Favorite
data.text:
Asian Food at a Great Value. Their Egg Drop Soup is the best!
Haven't had anything that I disliked but the Garlic Pork is my favorite! Good Egg Rolls too!

data.title: Good Food
data.text: Close your eyes when you go in. Not the cleanest in the world, but good food. It's been here a while and has a good name. Good amount of space for parking which is great during the lunch hour. Worth it.

data.title: Friendly server, fast service
data.text:
Woman at counter was very courteous and full of smiles. Nice talking to her while waiting. Speaking of which, I only had to wait about 5 minutes for these wings. But they still tasted fresh and meaty. You get 8 for $4.50, which is pretty standard. 

As usual, I got these to-go. When I got home, I put the wings in the oven at 270 degrees for about 15 minutes. They were hot as new, but to be honest I did have to use a paper towel between the wings and the plate, just to reduce the Grease for Peace factor.

I got the fried noodles, which were 95 cents rather than 75 or 50 like the competitors. But still worth the price, since they were fat ones. Nice and wide...

As for the Yum Yum sauce, it's a spicy combination of mayo, ketchup, and peppers. Cost is 75 cents per about 4 ounce (?) styo cup; decent portion. Worth the money to give it a try.

I'm giving Top Wok 4 owl eyes, 'cuz it was a pleasurable experience from purchase to the last bite and burp. Hope you feel the same.

data.title: Always good.
data.text: Quick friendly service, good tasting food, Some food can be ordered with no MSG added, sorry not the specials. Oh, and when item on menu is marked hot, it is! Standard variety, some in teresting specials keep fresh. I visit every month or so. Well priced for proportion size, generous, Take out, drive thru, or dine in clean simple dinning room.

data.title: Don't judge a book by its cover... seriously.
data.text:
Honestly, from the outside and the décor of the inside, this place might turn away many people.

Yet, their food is a surprising treat.

When you walk in, orders are taken at a counter in "fast food" fashion, but the food is prepared fresh and to order.

They really need to modernize the exterior and interior, but their food does not need any improvement at all due to it being tasty, flavorful, and delivered to your table in nice large portions.

My wife, who is Thai and a vegetarian, had a tofu version of General Tso chicken.  I had the spice beef.  Both where cooked and prepared properly and had much flavor.

I wasn't thrilled for the $1.00 charge for my wife's glass of water (she does not drink anything other than water), but that would be my only criticism of what was a fine and cost-effective meal.

data.title: Fast, fresh and delicious
data.text: Huge menu, great prices, generous portions.  Everything tasted delicious - cooked fresh when you order, but still fast!

data.title: You get what you pay for
data.text:
The review was 4 star, but I can only rate it a 2.5-star.  Food was average but very cheap.  I totally didn't expect to find this place was a combo (optional)  drive-through and low cost meal that also provided seating inside.  People were nice but we weren't that excited about the taste of the food.  
Go there if you just want a quick, cheap meal, but not if you want to have a nicer chinese meal.   Food was nice and hot, but Kung Pao chicken was a lot of Kung Pao and not much chicken.

data.title: Super fresh and the staff are very friendly
data.text: I love going here with friends because it is a chance to share and try different things.  They can tweak the order if there is something new you want to try--they were out of asparagus one time and substituted green beans, wow, really great!
